Subject: StealthAUDIT (SA) UI pop up error when navigating the job nodes
Description: hexadecimal value 0x00, is an invalid character. Line 1
What_We_Know__c:
Sanjay Meghani 11:37 AM
The PublishedReports.xml could be corrupted. You can open it in the web browser and see if it throws an error too.
Solution_Comment__c:
onfirmed that the current version of Stealth application(s) running in the Environment:

Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) 11.5.0.240

As directed by R&D we found that the Web UI was not able to load either in relation to the “hexadecimal value 0x00, is an invalid character. Line 1” error.

The correction was to rebuild the Reports Folder under the install path  D:STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITReports  the original folder was renamed ap[pending _03132025 to the end.
Closed and reopened the SA Console to rebuild the folder.

We then re-published the reports under the .Active Directory Inventory Job Group 
•	Publish – Publishes the reports from the selected job group or job without regenerating the report. See the Reporting topic for additional information.
Netwrix Enterprise Auditor v11.6 > Administration > Navigating the Console > Navigation Pane > Jobs Tree Right-click Menus  > Jobs Tree Primary Nodes
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Admin/Navigate/Pane.htm 

Additional Reports can be re-published manually or rebuilt when the related Job completes next.
